summary.summary: ch-praneeth-08 maintains exclusive ownership with four commits in the past week, all landing on today's fresh main branch with zero staleness. Recent velocity reveals sustained focus on production hygieneâ€”stripping debug console statements from algorithm triggers and Gantt chart handlers alongside legacy routing removal. Zero open pull requests or issues confirms work proceeds in isolation without code review or collaboration safety nets. This concentrates critical deployment knowledge in a single contributor while the codebase stabilizes. Momentum is steady but carries acute bus factor risk without peer validation.
highlights: ch-praneeth-08 delivered four consecutive production-hygiene commits eliminating debug artifacts and legacy routing infrastructure
Main branch shows zero staleness with commits from today and no open PR or issue debt
Cleanup specifically targets Gantt chart and algorithm visualization components for deployment readiness
concerns: Sole contributor workflow concentrates all knowledge in ch-praneeth-08 without code review or backup
Absence of open issues or PRs indicates zero external feedback or collaboration touchpoints

summary.headline: Solo contributor maintaining while legacy branches rot.
summary.summary: Lalithaditya007 is currently the sole active contributor with 5 commits this week, while previous drivers ch-praneeth-08 and Shashipreetham1 have gone silent after building the core platform. PR #1 is open and ready for review, indicating continued forward momentum on the auditorium booking features. However, three branches (aditya1, shashi, test) have been abandoned for over six months, creating repository clutter and increasing technical debt. The shift from the multi-contributor team that delivered 45 commits of features to single-person maintenance presents a significant bus factor risk.
highlights: 5 commits in the last 7 days showing active development
PR #1 open and ready for review indicating ongoing feature work
Zero open issues demonstrating clean current codebase state
concerns: Bus factor risk: Only Lalithaditya007 active this week versus previous multi-contributor pattern
Three stale branches (aditya1, shashi, test) abandoned for 185+ days cluttering repository
Previous core contributors ch-praneeth-08 and Shashipreetham1 currently inactive
summary.recommendation: Review and merge PR #1 today, then delete stale branches aditya1, shashi, and test to reduce technical debt.

summary.headline: High commit velocity overshadowed by 300 open PRs and review backlog.
summary.summary: The repository maintains strong activity with 544 commits from 52 contributors this week, led by mjbvz (55), osortega (53), and bpasero (47). Core AI chat development continues steadilyâ€”daviddossett advances attachment toolbar and model picker UX while meganrogge drives accessibility improvementsâ€”but momentum is threatened by severe review bottlenecks. Over 300 open PRs include high-severity blockers stalled for 30+ days without activity, risking code rot and contributor fatigue.
highlights: 544 commits from 52 contributors demonstrates sustained high velocity across the codebase
daviddossett and sandy081 shipping improvements to chat attachments and session management
mjbvz completed major infrastructure migration from webpack to esbuild for faster builds
concerns: 300 open PRs indicate critical review capacity constraints
Multiple PRs from external contributors stalled 30+ days without maintainer feedback
High volume of long-running Copilot-generated PRs may be overwhelming human review bandwidth
blockers: PR #289163 open for 31 days with no recent activity from author murataslan1, blocking feature integration
PR #291618 branch inactive for 22 days regarding agent sessions state fallback, requiring review or closure decision
PR #294073 stalled for 10 days fixing Windows context evaluation, blocking platform-specific bug resolution
summary.recommendation: Schedule an immediate team-wide PR triage session today to clear PRs older than 30 days by merging viable contributions and closing abandoned drafts.

The single-contributor model creates a critical knowledge silo, and the lack of recent velocity confirms the project has stalled before reaching launch. No open issues or PRs indicate work is not currently in flight, jeopardizing the timeline.

Production API integration and environment-based configuration completed
Clean repository state with zero technical debt or open issues
concerns: 27-day commit gap means development has stalled
Single contributor (ch-praneeth-08) creates bus factor risk
No visible work in progress despite launch-ready infrastructure
summary.recommendation: Ch-praneeth-08 should immediately share local work-in-progress or schedule a team sync to identify hidden blockers and redistribute workload.

Three feature branchesâ€”auth-face, student-flow, and teacher-flowâ€”have been abandoned for 162 days, indicating unfinished parallel work was never integrated or cleaned up. The silence suggests either a paused project or uncommitted local work that needs to be pushed immediately.

data.headline: Add global.core shim for GitHub Actions compatibility in MCP servers

fileChanges.action: Adds compatibility shim providing global.core mock for standalone Node.js execution
Requires shim module before other imports to initialize global.core
Requires shim module before other imports to initialize global.core
Adds global.core mock setup and clears mocks in beforeEach hook
Adds shim.cjs to safe-inputs and safe-outputs file deployment lists

data.keyInsight: The shim enables code written for GitHub Actions' github-script context (which expects a built-in global.core object) to run correctly in standalone Node.js processes like MCP servers. It is a no-op when running inside GitHub Actions and provides console-based fallbacks when running standalone.

commitMeta.message: Add global.core shim for Node.js/GitHub Actions compatibility

summary.headline: Extreme velocity with Copilot driving 439 commits and humans anchoring quality.
summary.summary: The repository is operating at extreme velocity with 439 commits in the past seven days, led primarily by Copilot (259 commits) with substantial human oversight from Mossaka (41), dsyme (30), and pelikhan (29). While 16 active contributors maintain strong momentum across documentation, GraphQL fixes, and core shim development, the issue backlog has grown to 59 open items and three asset branches have lingered without pull requests for 59-86 days. The team is successfully managing 7 concurrent open PRs including critical fixes for base branch detection, though two remain marked as work-in-progress without clear completion criteria.
highlights: 439 commits in 7 days demonstrates exceptional shipping velocity across 16 contributors
Copilot and human developers (Mossaka, dsyme, pelikhan) maintaining effective collaborative rhythm on ARM64 and GraphQL features
Active daily development across multiple asset workflows with zero branch staleness flags
concerns: 59 open issues accumulating without visible triage or assignment patterns
Three asset branches (documentation-unbloat, skillz generator, dev) idle for 59-86 days without associated PRs
PR 17353 marked [WIP] in title but not as draft, creating status ambiguity
summary.recommendation: Convert the three dormant asset branches older than eight weeks into draft PRs or archive them to maintain branch hygiene.

data.headline: Updates GitHub Actions runner compatibility matrix and documents macOS virtualization limitations

fileChanges.action: Documents GitHub Actions runner support status including macOS incompatibility and ARM64 full support

data.keyInsight: Documents that GitHub-hosted macOS runners lack nested virtualization required for Docker, rendering them incompatible. Updates ARM64 architecture status to fully supported based on ubuntu-24.04-arm testing.

commitMeta.message: docs: update runner and architecture compatibility
commitMeta.author: Mossaka

data.headline: Auto-generates JVM build tool proxy configs when HTTP_PROXY is present

fileChanges.action: Adds proxy config generation for Maven, Gradle, and sbt

data.keyInsight: Java build tools ignore HTTP_PROXY environment variables; this generates required Maven settings.xml, Gradle properties, and JVM options automatically, with chroot-aware paths.

summary.headline: High velocity overshadowed by critical unassigned issues and stale dependency PRs.
summary.summary: The team shipped 38 commits across 5 contributors this week, with Mossaka driving 17 commits focused on Java proxy configurations and documentation. However, Issues #332 and #348 remain unassigned for 34 and 33 days respectively, creating critical blockers. PR #963 containing JVM proxy fixes sits stale alongside dependency updates #952 and #939. CI pipelines are failing on eastus runner timeouts while multiple agentic workflows report failures, indicating infrastructure strain despite strong feature momentum.
highlights: Mossaka delivered 17 commits including Maven/Gradle/sbt proxy pre-configuration for corporate environments
Version 0.20.2 shipped with expanded ARM64 Linux and macOS support
38 commits in 7 days demonstrates sustained development velocity across 5 active contributors
concerns: Issues #332 and #348 unassigned for 34 and 33 days respectively without ownership
PR #963 (JVM proxy fix) stale for 2 days while PRs #952 and #939 idle for 3 days
CI failing on gh-aw action download timeouts and multiple agentic workflows broken
blockers: Issue #332 has remained unassigned for 34 days without ownership or progress
Issue #348 has remained unassigned for 33 days blocking backlog hygiene
PR #963 containing JVM proxy fixes by Copilot is stale with 2 days of inactivity
summary.recommendation: Assign owners to Issues #332 and #348 or close them today, and merge or close stale PRs #952, #939, and #963.

data.keyInsight: Upgrades the release automation action to v2.5.0; verify v2 breaking changes don't affect release artifact uploads.

data.headline: Replace Rust one-shot-token library with hardened C implementation featuring XOR obfuscation

fileChanges.action: Add *.so pattern for C shared library build outputs
Replace Rust multi-stage build with inline GCC compilation using hardening flags
Remove Rust package configuration
Update documentation for C build and XOR obfuscation security measures
Rewrite to use GCC with hardening flags and verify no cleartext tokens remain
Add script to generate XOR-obfuscated byte arrays for default token names
Implement XOR obfuscation, hidden symbol visibility, and complete secure_getenv interception
Deleted LD_PRELOAD library intercepting getenv to cache and clear sensitive tokens

data.keyInsight: The library was rewritten from Rust to C to eliminate the Docker dependency on the Rust toolchain, while adding runtime XOR-deobfuscation of token names and compiler hardening flags to prevent extraction of sensitive strings via strings(1) or objdump. This eliminates the security mechanism that cached API tokens on first access and removed them from the process environment, leaving sensitive credentials exposed in /proc/self/environ for the process lifetime.

commitMeta.message: fix: harden one-shot-token binary against ELF reconnaissance (#776)
commitMeta.author: Mossaka

data.headline: Re-enables OpenAI proxy routing and isolates Codex API keys through sidecar

fileChanges.action: Re-enables CODEX_API_KEY check in agent environment credential isolation validation
Updates tests to expect OPENAI_BASE_URL and Codex key proxy routing
Re-enables OPENAI_BASE_URL and excludes CODEX_API_KEY from agent environment

data.keyInsight: Removes temporary Codex credential bypass so all API keys route through the proxy sidecar, restoring proper credential isolation while re-enabling OpenAI proxy support.

commitMeta.message: feat: disable codex credential sharing, enable proxied calls (#854)
commitMeta.author: Claude

data.headline: Remove ~/.claude.json bind mount to fix atomic write issues

fileChanges.action: Removed ~/.claude.json file creation and bind mount logic
Updated comment about config file overwrite behavior

data.keyInsight: File bind mounts on Linux prevent atomic writes (temp file + rename) required by Claude Code. The writable home volume now handles ~/.claude.json creation via entrypoint instead.

commitMeta.message: fix: remove .claude.json file bind mount regression (#911)
commitMeta.author: Mossaka

data.headline: Documents AWF_ONE_SHOT_TOKEN_DEBUG environment variable for token caching troubleshooting

fileChanges.action: Documents AWF_ONE_SHOT_TOKEN_DEBUG debug logging configuration options
Adds token caching troubleshooting guide using debug logging

data.keyInsight: Documents the AWF_ONE_SHOT_TOKEN_DEBUG environment variable to help troubleshoot one-shot-token library issues with sensitive token caching and cleanup.

data.headline: Refactors release workflow into parallel jobs with shared version outputs

fileChanges.action: Splits monolithic job into 6 parallel jobs using needs dependencies and job outputs

data.keyInsight: Version extraction now runs in a dedicated setup job that exposes outputs to dependent jobs, enabling parallel Docker builds for squid, agent, api-proxy and agent-act images. Node.js setup and npm install moved to the final release job only.

commitMeta.message: perf: parallelize container image builds in release workflow (#909)
commitMeta.author: Mossaka
